NC

\[ C = \int_{0}^T f(t_1;\lambda,\mu,\tau_0) c(t_1;\lambda,\mu,\tau_0) dt_1 + \int_T^\infty f(t_1;\lambda,\mu,\tau_0) dt1 \]

where

\[ c_i(t_i;\lambda,\mu,\tau_i) = \int_{0}^{T-t_{i-1}} f(t_i;\lambda,\mu,\tau_i) c_{i-1}(t_i;\lambda,\mu,\tau_0) dt_i + \int_{T-t_{i-1}}^\infty f(t_1;\lambda,\mu,\tau_0) dti \] Prop: \(c_i = 1, \forall i\).

Proof:

suppose there exist \(i\) s.t \(c_i<1\), then there exists a sequence \(t_k,t_{k+1},...\) such that \(c()<1, \forall i\), but by definitions this sequence is monotone, so it converges. That means that \(\Delta t_i = t_i - t_{i-1} \displaystyle\rightarrow 0 \text{ as } i \rightarrow \infty\)

NC, after 14/11 Ernst email.

norma.const <- function(lambda,mu,CT,n,truncdim = FALSE){
  lg = NULL
  lf = NULL
  for(i in 1:n){
    df = sim.tree.g(lambda,mu,CT) # simulation of tree
    lg[i] = g_samp_missobs(df,c(lambda,mu)) # calculate sampling probability 
    # and calculate joint probability 
    to = df$to[-nrow(df)]
    to[to==2] = 1
    lf[i] = -emphasis:::nllik.tree(pars=c(lambda,mu,Inf),tree=list(wt=diff(c(0,df$bt)),to=to),truncdim = truncdim)
  }
  # finally, get the approximation
  const.approx = sum(exp(lf-lg))/n
  variance = sum((exp(lf-lg)-const.approx)^2)/n
  return(list(nconst=const.approx,var=variance))
}


sim.tree.g <- function(lambda,mu,CT){
  Ne = rpois(1,mu*CT) # number of extinct species
  Np = rpois(1,(mu+lambda)*CT) # number of present species
  brts = runif(Np,min=0,max=CT) # branching times of speciation of present species
  ms = runif(Ne,min=0,max=CT) # branching times of speciation of extinct species
  me = runif(Ne,min=ms,max=CT) # branching times of extinctions
  # return matrix with branching times and topology
  to = c(rep(1,Ne),rep(0,Ne))
  df = data.frame(bt = c(ms,me),to=to)
  df = rbind(df,data.frame(bt=c(brts,CT),to=c(rep(2,length(brts)),2)))
  df = df[order(df$bt),]
  return(df)
}

g_samp_missobs <- function(df,pars){
  # sampling probability 
  last = nrow(df)
  ct = df[last,1]
  Ne = sum(df$to==0)
  Np = sum(df$to==2) - 1
  subdf_e = df[df$to==1,]
  subdf_p = df[df$to==2,]
  Ts = ct-subdf_e$bt
  to = df$to[-last]
  rto = to
  to[to==2] = 1
  n = c(2,2+cumsum(to)+cumsum(to-1))
  nm = n[c(rto,2)==1]
  log_dens_miss = dpois(Ne,lambda = pars[2]*ct,log=TRUE)-Ne*log(ct)-sum(log(Ts))-sum(log(nm))+lgamma(Ne+1)
  ne = n[c(rto,0)==2]
  log_dens_obs = dpois(Np,lambda = (pars[1]+pars[2])*ct,log=TRUE)-Np*log(ct)-sum(log(ne))+lgamma(Np+1)
  log_dens = log_dens_miss+log_dens_obs
  return(log_dens)
}

sim.tree.g <- function(lambda,mu,CT,seed){
  set.seed(seed)
  Ne = rpois(1,mu*CT) # number of extinct species
  Np = rpois(1,(mu+lambda)*CT) # number of present species
  brts = runif(Np,min=0,max=CT) # branching times of speciation of present species
  ms = runif(Ne,min=0,max=CT) # branching times of speciation of extinct species
  me = runif(Ne,min=ms,max=CT) # branching times of extinctions
  # return matrix with branching times and topology
  to = c(rep(1,Ne),rep(0,Ne))
  df = data.frame(bt = c(ms,me),to=to)
  df = rbind(df,data.frame(bt=c(brts,CT),to=c(rep(2,length(brts)),2)))
  df = df[order(df$bt),]
  return(df)
}
p.norma.const <- function(lambda,mu,CT,n,truncdim = FALSE,initseed=1){
  time=proc.time()
  # Calculate the number of cores
  no_cores <- detectCores()   # - 1
  
  # Initiate cluster
  cl <- makeCluster(no_cores)
  clusterExport(cl, "mu")
  clusterExport(cl, "lambda")
  clusterExport(cl, "CT")
  clusterExport(cl, "g_samp_missobs")
 # clusterExport(cl, "truncdim")
  
  nc1s <- function(seed){
    df = emphasis:::sim.tree.g(lambda,mu,CT,seed) # simulation of tree
    lg = g_samp_missobs(df,c(lambda,mu)) # calculate sampling probability 
    # and calculate joint probability 
    to = df$to[-nrow(df)]
    to[to==2] = 1
    lf = -emphasis:::nllik.tree(pars=c(lambda,mu,Inf),tree=list(wt=diff(c(0,df$bt)),to=to))
    return(exp(lf-lg))
  }
  #library(parallel)
  
  vals = parSapply(cl, initseed:(initseed+n),nc1s)
  stopCluster(cl)
    # finally, get the approximation
  const.approx = sum(vals)/n
  variance = (sum(vals-const.approx)^2)/n
  time = get.time(time)
  
  return(list(nconst=const.approx,var=variance,time=time))
}

nee et al. likelihood

#' @title Pt
#' @author Giovanni Laudanno
#' @description Nee's function: pt
#' @inheritParams default_params_doc
#' @return pt
#' @export
pt  <- function (lambda, mu, t) {
  time <- t
  Lambda <- exp((mu - lambda) * time)
  out    <- (lambda == mu) * (1/(1 + lambda * time)) +
    (lambda != mu) * ((lambda - mu + (lambda == mu))/(lambda - mu *
                                                        Lambda * (lambda != mu) + (lambda == mu)))
  return(unname(out))
}

#' @title ut
#' @author Giovanni Laudanno
#' @description Nee's function: ut
#' @inheritParams default_params_doc
#' @return ut
#' @export
ut  <- function (lambda, mu, t) {
  time <- t
  Lambda <- exp((mu - lambda) * time)
  out    <- (lambda == mu) * (lambda * time/(1 + lambda * time)) +
    (lambda != mu) * ((lambda - lambda * Lambda + (lambda == mu)) /
                        (lambda - mu * Lambda * (lambda != mu) + (lambda == mu)))
  return(unname(out))
}

#' @title Pn
#' @author Giovanni Laudanno
#' @description Nee's function: pn
#' @inheritParams default_params_doc
#' @return pn
#' @export
pn <- function(lambda, mu, t, n) {
  out <- (n > 0) * sls::pt(t = t, lambda = lambda, mu = mu) *
    (1 - sls::ut(t = t, lambda = lambda, mu = mu)) *
    sls::ut(t = t, lambda = lambda, mu = mu)^(n - 1 + 2*(n == 0)) +
    (n == 0) * (1 - sls::pt(t = t, lambda = lambda, mu = mu))
  return(out)
}

Nee_likelihood <- function(lambda, mu, brts, cond)
{
  BRTS <- c(brts[1], brts)
  NN <- length(BRTS)
  out <- prod(
    pt(lambda = lambda, mu = mu, t = BRTS) * (1 - ut(lambda = lambda, mu
                                                     = mu, t = BRTS))
  ) * lambda^(NN - 2) #* factorial(NN - 1)
  out <- out/((pt(lambda = lambda, mu = mu, t = BRTS[1]))^(2 * cond))
}

lambda <- 1; mu <- 0.1; brts <- 5:1; cond <- 0
mus <- seq(0,1,0.1); res1 <- res2 <- rep(NA, length(mus))
for (i in seq_along(mus))
{
  mu <- mus[i]
  res1[i] <- log(Nee_likelihood(lambda = lambda, mu = mu, brts = brts,
                                cond = cond))
  res2[i] <- DDD:::dd_loglik(pars = c(lambda, mu, Inf), pars2 = emphasis::pars2, brts = brts, missnumspec = 0)
}
plot(mus, res1,ylim=c(min(res2,res1),max(res1,res2))); lines(mus, res2, col = 'red')
